<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Searches | Radiology Workflow Assistant</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Download Searches for macOS, including blank starter data files for your own pattern library and study logs." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <div class="bg-glow bg-glow-a" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="bg-glow bg-glow-b" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <header class="site-header">
    <img src="images/icon.png" alt="Searches App Icon" class="app-icon" />
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Radiology Utility</p>
      <h1>Searches</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A focused desktop assistant for search patterns, study tracking, and faster reads.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="content">
    <section class="card primary">
      <h2>Download for macOS</h2>
      <p>The app package includes blank starter files so each user can build a personal workflow from scratch.</p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="btn btn-main" href="downloads/Searches-macOS.zip">Download Searches-macOS.zip</a>
      </div>
      <ul class="meta-list">
        <li>Starter file 1: <a href="downloads/radiology_search_patterns.h5">radiology_search_patterns.h5</a> (blank and ready)</li>
        <li>Starter file 2: <a href="downloads/study_times.csv">study_times.csv</a> (header-only template)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>First Launch</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Open the app and begin creating your own patterns.</li>
          <li>Or use File > Import Search Patterns (.h5).</li>
          <li>Use File > Import Study Log CSV for your own study log.</li>
        </ol>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Data Storage</h3>
        <p>User-editable files are copied on first run into your local app data folder:</p>
        <p class="path">~/.radiology_assistant/</p>
        <p>This keeps app updates separate from user data.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Install</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Download the zip.</li>
          <li>Drag Searches.app into Applications.</li>
          <li>Right-click > Open the first time to bypass Gatekeeper prompts.</li>
        </ol>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <p>Searches for radiology workflows.</p>
  </footer>

  <script src="js/site.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
